The paper deals with a communication problem involving noisy channels and rate constraints, which is a common theme in information theory (cs.IT). The problem involves a remote source and distortion measures, which are also common in multimedia processing (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of logarithmic loss penalty criterion suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR), where such measures are commonly used. Finally, the paper involves optimization and mathematical analysis, which could also place it in the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SI).
